Pre-heat oven to 350 degrees F. Season pork tenderloins with salt and pepper. Heat a 10 to 12 inch straight-sided saute pan; add 1 tablespoon oil and brown meat evenly on all sides. Remove pork from pan and degrease. Add remaining oil and saute carrots, onions and garlic for 3 to 4 minutes. Add chicken broth and Dannon(R) Plain Yogurt; bring to a boil. Re-add pork, cover and transfer to oven and bake, 55 to 60 minutes until fork tender. Remove pork from pan and keep warm. Place pan juices and vegetables in a blender and puree until smooth (add more chicken stock if necessary to thin). Slice pork and top with sauce. Serve with parslied noodles.